postcontent: Short version: Norinco sks with sgworks stock installed. Foregrip, tri rail, ext mag release, flip up iron sights, 4 mags, red/green dot sight, x4 zoom scope (flip to side ). Sks bolt milled to take magazines with bolt action open or closed. Every year I treat myself to a fun modification project and sell the gun to do the next one. This year I turned an sks with a broken tapco stock into a bullpup rifle with a barrell length of 16 inches. I'm selling it with 4 magazines. To be honest the 20 rounders are perfect, and I have a plastic and metal 30 rounder. The plastic has done well, but needed machined out of the box to fit. title: For Sale:  SAVAGE MODEL 12 VLP. STAINLESS 26" FLUTED HEAVY BARREL
location: North of Dayton,  Sidney, Ohio, United States
postcontent:
For sale is a beautiful savage model 12 VLP(varmint low profile).  This is the model with the internal magazine which can only be purchased by special order now.  It is chambered in 22-250.  The mass produce VLP is now only produced with a detachable box magazine, but you can still get the internal mag by ordering it.

It has a 26" fluted stainless heavy barrel.  It has the accutrigger.  Wood laminate stock( by far savages most attractive stock).  The stock does have one scratch which is hard to see but I show it in the pictures because I try to represent the firearms I sell as accurately as possible.  Other than the one scratch this gun is flawless and the 22-250 is a deadly fast and flat shooting round for both bench rest shooting and varmint hunting.  I had a redfield revenge scope on the rifle but I am keeping that scope but will be selling it with a bushnell scope (shown in pictures).

The gun itself retails for $1,000 without a scope.  The scope was $175.  However, it is a used rifle with a used scope and one blemish in the stock.  It is still a beautiful and deadly accurate gun.  I am asking $875 OBO which is significantly less than it would cost if you went to your local gun shop and bought this combo.  The only reason I am selling is because I just bought the model 10XP to use for hunting.  This gun is just too nice to take out to the woods.  I have more pictures and will forward them to you just too big to upload.

Thanks for your time and I would consider trades but no junk.  No hi points etc.i am not interested in 22's.
